{
  "text": "Not only flies but also cockroaches are regarded as common vectors of different microorganisms, including P. mirabilis and P. vulgaris strains, carrying them on their bodies and posing a threat of their dissemination, food contamination, and spoiling as well as infection of humans. The bacteria were found in Nigerian cockroaches in Ekpoma, a village characterized by poor sanitary conditions [CITATION_1] , and in Iranian brown-banded cockroaches collected in kitchens of Ahvaz houses [CITATION_2] . Wannigama et al. [CITATION_3] reported on the isolation of P. mirabilis from 8.9 % cockroaches found in households and food-handling establishments in Varanasi, India.",
